        <mxCell id="b7xK3bh1fwTg6WPPIEsJ-5" value="&lt;i&gt;Compute calls &lt;b&gt;ComputeConsequences. &lt;/b&gt;Probably easiest to add reconstruction logic here. This would add new columns to the &lt;b&gt;consequences.Result &lt;/b&gt;object that is returned from &lt;b&gt;Compute&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/i&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;b&gt;StreamAbstract&lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp;sends the result object directly to the results writer, so this would authomattically add reconstruction information to a basic consequences assessment. However, if we implement &lt;b&gt;StreamAbstractLifecycle&lt;/b&gt;, we could parse the &lt;b&gt;Result&lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp;object before passing it to whatever format of &lt;b&gt;ResultsWriter(s)&lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp;we end up using.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="text;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;spacingLeft=4;spacingRight=4;overflow=hidden;points=[[0,0.5],[1,0.5]];portConstraint=eastwest;rotatable=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" vertex="1" parent="4oVQOs9NOsqmQCFZLNWR-1">
          <mxGeometry y="52" width="250" height="230" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
