        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="b7xK3bh1fwTg6WPPIEsJ-2" value="A new type of &lt;span style=&quot;font-style: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;ResultsWriter &lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;may be necessary. Multifrequency analysis adds columns to the result for each hazard, but this will be unwieldy for the number of results included in lifecycle analyses.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;It also may be possible to use existing &lt;span style=&quot;font-style: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;ResultsWriters &lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;and adapt for purpose using logic within the &lt;span style=&quot;font-style: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;StreamProcessor &lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;function. e.g.:&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;white-space: pre;&quot;&gt;&#x9;&lt;/span&gt;- summarize lifecycle results and save as columns in the standard &lt;span style=&quot;font-style: normal;&quot;&gt;SpatialResultsWriter.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-style: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;white-space: pre;&quot;&gt;&#x9;&lt;/span&gt;- &lt;/span&gt;Save results from individual iterations in separate file which can be joined to the spatial file for further analysis. (Not sure if any existing &lt;span style=&quot;font-style: normal;&quot;&gt;ResultsWriters&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;would work for this)&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="text;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=top;spacingLeft=4;spacingRight=4;overflow=hidden;rotatable=0;points=[[0,0.5],[1,0.5]];portConstraint=eastwest;fontStyle=2;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" vertex="1" parent="4oVQOs9NOsqmQCFZLNWR-18">
